title: For Sale:  Fine U.S. Harpers Ferry Model 1842 Percussion Musket Dated 1847 (Mex-Am war era) with Bayo
location: Morris County, New Jersey, United States
postcontent: Excellent condition (see pics) 1842 model marked 1847 Harpers Ferry Percussion Musket. Complete with original bayonet.The Model 1842 Musket has the distinction of being the first regulation percussion firearm manufactured in a national armory, the first musket manufactured at the U.S. Armories at Springfield and Harpers Ferry with completely interchangeable components and the last .69 caliber, smoothbore musket issued by the U.S. Army. The Model 1842 musket was the primary infantry weapon of both the Union and Confederate armies during the first two years of the Civil War. It was still used in significant numbers by both armies as late as 1863 and was not fully supplanted by the .58 caliber rifle-musket at the end of the war. This musket has standard bright barrel, lock and furniture and a black walnut, oil finished stock. The lock plate is marked: "HARPERS / FERRY / 1847" in three vertical lines at the rear of the hammer and "eagle and shield / "U.S." is stamped in front of the hammer. The barrel tang is dated "1847" and the left rear of the barrel is marked with "V / P / "eagle head" proof and inspection marks as well as a script "AR" over "P". The buttplate is stamped "U.S." ahead of the upper screw. The left stock flat has a faint oval cartouche.

title: For Sale:  Springfield M1A EBR For Sale!!
postcontent: Selling my Springfield M1A EBR Platform Rifle!!! This is the Standard Model M1A with 20” GI barrel dropped into the Sage EBR Mod 0 stock. This is the rock solid setup that the U.S Military used to repurpose many of the M14 rifles that were in storage and bring them up to a modern platform with increased accuracy.This M1A EBR features an adjustable stock and adjustable cheekpiece, pistol grip, and plenty of picatinny rail space for added gear. Included with the stock is the Sage Detachable Cantilever Sight Base (DCSB) that provides an absolute rock steady solution for mounting a scope to the rifle. (The scope pictured is also included with the sale). The attached scope is a Nikon Monarch 3 4x-16x BDC reticle and has been sighted in at 100 yards.A few internal upgrades to the rifle were also added such as a Sadlak Op Rod Spring Guide and a SEI Muzzle Brake. title: For Sale:  Scorpion 9x18 Czech Pistol, unfired
postcontent: Original CZ Scorpion model vs 61 was developed by Czechoslovakia in the late 1950's as an easily concealed submachine gun.  Chambered for the 9x18 Makarov caliber, this is a semi-auto copy.  New, unfired.  Similar design to the MP5K, but much smaller, lighter, easier to handle, and about a third the price.  Check YouTube for bump fire videos, apparently the design makes it obtainable without special stock.  It utilizes the telescoping bolt like the Uzi.  Overall length of 10.75 inches, barrel length of 4.53 inches, weight of 2.54 pounds without magazine and 3.15 pounds with fully loaded mag.  The frame is drilled and tapped for attaching the folding stock mounting plate.Included is the OEM hard case, 2 - 20 rd magazines, mag pouch, holster that can be worn either as a hip or thigh holster, bore brush, users manual, Czech Small Arms decal, and 5 years manufacturer's warranty.Civilian (Semi-auto) models of Skorpion (European) Scorpion (USA) have been produced by Czech-USA in three calibers: 7.65 Br, 9x17, and 9x18 Makarov.  Of those three calibers, the 9x18 has the most reasonably priced ammo.  Everyone would like to have the Skorpion in 9x19 or 9mm Luger.  Efforts were made by the Czechs to manufacture a 9x19 version, but the size had to be greatly increased to handle the higher pressure of the round.  There is a U.S. company "Armitage" that produced a 9x19 pistol they called a "Scorpion".  Only 602 were produced, there is usually a couple listed on line.  Reviews I have seen on that pistol, said you were lucky to empty a mag without a stoppage.This model is "out of stock" at CzechPoint.  Since the pistol is manufactured using some surplus parts, there will come a time that new ones will no longer be available.  Get yours while you can.  Through a SNAFU, I ended up with two, that is the only reason this one is for sale. $625 FTF in NW Columbus.  OBROShipped to FFL at buyer's expense.Trade:  Military high power9mm or .45 1911
